Polk Award, the National

00:00:26.590 --> 00:00:27.401
Magazine Award.

00:00:27.401 --> 00:00:28.900
She was named
Journalist of the Year

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:31.700
by the National Association
of Black Journalists in 2015

00:00:31.700 --> 00:00:35.740
and named to The Root
in both 2015 and 2016.

00:00:35.740 --> 00:00:39.610
She is also a 2017 New
American Emerson fellow.

00:00:39.610 --> 00:00:42.220
She's in the process of writing
a book entitled "The Problem

00:00:42.220 --> 00:00:45.010
We All Live With" to be
published on the One World

00:00:45.010 --> 00:00:47.890
imprint of Penguin Random House.

00:00:47.890 --> 00:00:50.230
Last year, Nikole helped
found the Ida B. Wells

00:00:50.230 --> 00:00:52.960
Society for Investigative
Reporting, a training

00:00:52.960 --> 00:00:55.000
and mentorship
organization geared

00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:57.400
toward increasing the number
of investigative reporters

00:00:57.400 --> 00:00:58.480
of color.

00:00:58.480 --> 00:01:03.290
I'm so proud to be here as a
mom of two young kids of color,

00:01:03.290 --> 00:01:05.620
trying to choose a
school for my kids.

00:01:05.620 --> 00:01:08.060
And I'm so glad that we
have allies in the audience,

00:01:08.060 --> 00:01:09.250
so thank you.

00:01:09.250 --> 00:01:10.061
Nikole?

00:01:10.061 --> 00:01:14.871
