00:50:08.860 --> 00:50:10.270
you're also afraid that
too many white people

00:50:10.270 --> 00:50:11.145
are going to come in.

00:50:11.145 --> 00:50:11.680
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:11.680 --> 00:50:12.179
Right?

00:50:12.179 --> 00:50:13.000
And I'm like, yes.

00:50:13.000 --> 00:50:13.900
That's exactly right.

00:50:13.900 --> 00:50:16.010
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:16.010 --> 00:50:17.290
This is not easy.

00:50:17.290 --> 00:50:19.340
It's not ever going to be easy.

00:50:19.340 --> 00:50:20.500
It's complicated.

00:50:20.500 --> 00:50:23.650
It took us-- if you look
at my Twitter handle,

00:50:23.650 --> 00:50:26.590
I say that I write
about race from 1619,

00:50:26.590 --> 00:50:29.410
which is the year that the
first Africans were brought

00:50:29.410 --> 00:50:31.630
in this country to be enslaved.

00:50:31.630 --> 00:50:33.610
And this was when we
began implementing

00:50:33.610 --> 00:50:36.670
racial caste, which is
140 years before we even

00:50:36.670 --> 00:50:38.530
become a country, right?

00:50:38.530 --> 00:50:40.000
So this is older than us.

00:50:40.000 --> 00:50:42.850
This is embedded in the
DNA of this country.

00:50:42.850 --> 00:50:45.910
And we worked very,
very hard to create

00:50:45.910 --> 00:50:48.190
the inequality and
the segregation

00:50:48.190 --> 00:50:50.590
that we are dealing with now.

00:50:50.590 --> 00:50:52.930
We spent 400 years
perfecting it.

00:50:52.930 --> 00:50:56.950
We've spent maybe 40 years
trying half-heartedly

00:50:56.950 --> 00:50:57.790
to undo it.

00:50:57.790 --> 00:50:59.650
And then we somehow
just want it to be easy,

00:50:59.650 --> 00:51:02.500
because we just want to
be over with it already.

00:51:02.500 --> 00:51:04.820
It's not going to work that way.

00:51:04.820 --> 00:51:06.820
When we're putting these
communities and schools

00:51:06.820 --> 00:51:09.716
together, it's going to be
tense, it's going to be hard.

00:51:09.716 --> 00:51:11.840
It's going to-- like, we're
going to make mistakes.

00:51:11.840 --> 00:51:13.870
I'm saying we have
to do it, but it

00:51:13.870 --> 00:51:15.520
can't be the folks
who have always

00:51:15.520 --> 00:51:17.080
had the privilege
all the time say,

00:51:17.080 --> 00:51:18.910
you're so lucky that I'm here.

00:51:18.910 --> 00:51:21.430
And now let me tell
you that the last 20

00:51:21.430 --> 00:51:25.310
years of you working with
these kids is not good enough.

00:51:25.310 --> 00:51:27.242
And the only reason
that white parents

00:51:27.242 --> 00:51:29.200
are looking at that
school, which I write about

00:51:29.200 --> 00:51:30.752
in my article, is
they already had

00:51:30.752 --> 00:51:33.430
to have had a principle
that it worked miracles

00:51:33.430 --> 00:51:35.410
with that population to
even make white folks

00:51:35.410 --> 00:51:37.650
feel like this is even
an option for their kids.

00:51:37.650 --> 00:51:39.940
So that's the
issue, is how do you

00:51:39.940 --> 00:51:42.700
go in and understand,
I'm bringing privilege,

00:51:42.700 --> 00:51:44.590
I am bringing a lot of
assets to the school,

00:51:44.590 --> 00:51:47.890
but not overrun the people
who are already there?

00:51:47.890 --> 00:51:51.490
Where they can't necessarily
think about a community garden

00:51:51.490 --> 00:51:53.844
when they're just trying
to, like, you know,

00:51:53.844 --> 00:51:55.510
get their kids some
food in the morning,

00:51:55.510 --> 00:52:01.166
or when they're just trying
to get their kid's reading up.

00:52:01.166 --> 00:52:02.540
And they would
love those things,

00:52:02.540 --> 00:52:04.240
but that's not going
to be the priority.

00:52:04.240 --> 00:52:06.742
And then they fear those
things, because as someone

00:52:06.742 --> 00:52:08.200
who's living in
Bed-Stuy and, like,

00:52:08.200 --> 00:52:11.530
watching this dizzying
gentrification that's

00:52:11.530 --> 00:52:16.150
happening, watching my
neighbors, whom I love,

00:52:16.150 --> 00:52:19.120
who will knock on my window
and tell me to move my car,

00:52:19.120 --> 00:52:21.550
because I forgot to move
it, being pushed out

00:52:21.550 --> 00:52:24.400
of their homes, and then being
told that this is a good thing,

00:52:24.400 --> 00:52:26.950
because now the neighborhood's
becoming less poor, well, yes.

00:52:26.950 --> 00:52:28.330
But we see these signals, right?

00:52:28.330 --> 00:52:30.496
Yo see the bike lanes going
in, and you're like, OK.

00:52:30.496 --> 00:52:32.829
[LAUGHTER]

00:52:32.829 --> 00:52:34.870
Black folks have always
ridden bikes in Bed-Stuy,

00:52:34.870 --> 00:52:36.119
